  "note": "V3-EXQ-540a -- Option-b successor to V3-EXQ-540 (which was authored 2026-05-08 against Option-a use_mech307_signed_pe and never queued). The 2026-05-11 MECH-307 substrate landing implemented Gap 1 as Option-b (split VALENCE_POSITIVE_SURPRISE + VALENCE_NEGATIVE_SURPRISE channels). This experiment runs the same 3-arm gap-decomposition as V3-EXQ-540 under the now-canonical Option-b substrate path. ARM_1 flips use_mech307_split_surprise=True (Option-b) instead of use_mech307_signed_pe=True (Option-a); ARM_2 enables all three substrate-side sub-flags. The Gap-1 marker measurement also changes: n_split_surprise_centers (count of active centers with non-zero writes on either VALENCE_POSITIVE_SURPRISE or VALENCE_NEGATIVE_SURPRISE) is the discriminative observable, because under Option-b the legacy VALENCE_SURPRISE channel always receives the unsigned magnitude via the backward-compat write at the same site. 3-arm gap-decomposition successor to V3-EXQ-539 (which FAILed C5 approach_commit lift despite C1-C4 substrate counter PASS). This experiment exercises the consumer-side fix (Path B): the MECH-295 liking bridge's compute_conjunction_score_bias() reads the four-way conjunction at predicted-imminent locations and adds an additional approach bias when it holds. ARM_3 (SD-014 6-channel fallback) remains deferred -- if this experiment PARTIAL-PASSes (C1+C2 only), ARM_3 becomes the natural follow-on."
